  "rationale": "The base style is corporate-saas-clean with offGridExpansion LOCKED, so every section is reuse/adapt against the three seeded captured patterns \u2014 no novel, and off-grid treatments (stagger/overlap/bleed) stay on the sanctioned hero bookend only. Order sells the offering top-down: (1) an inverse hero bookend reuses hero-split-media-copy and is the sole accent-carrying, sole text-on-media (sanctioned display-title-over-media) section; (2) the three value_props render as ONE feature-item run of three open modules on cream (feature-item keeps it open collage, honoring no-cards-on-cream) adapted from features-split-feature; (3) a gallery-mosaic adapted from gallery-mosaic-with-overflow shows the work with a ghost-word watermark and a margin caption carrying the '10,000+ teams' proof \u2014 both baseline treatments legal under the lock; (4) WoodWave has no logo-wall, so social_proof maps onto an editorial testimonial split on a panel surface (quote + stat), flagging that gap rather than inventing a logo grid; (5) a centered conversion-stack (centering sanctioned for CTA) closes with the primary/secondary typographic links. All CTAs are links (no-buttons), radius 0, no shadows/gradients/hairlines, and only the hero display-title carries the accent."
